{SOUTH isn't strong enough to make a Reverse bid of 2\H at his second turn.

NORTH uses the 2\D (NMF) bid to ask SOUTH for further description. 
SOUTH should first show a 4-card \H suit, and next show 3-card \S support.

Change SOUTH's \H9 to the \S9 and the contract would be 4\S.}

